summary: I love and live for how The Last Jedi frames Ben’s moral choices in light of his love and potential happiness. He loves Rey and...
body:
I love and live for how The Last Jedi frames Ben’s moral choices in light of his love and potential happiness. He loves Rey and he wants to be happy with her and the only way to do that, the movie says, is through the straight and narrow path, through redemption, a true and deep change of heart that extends beyond just her. It tells us very clearly that love can’t survive if everything else in your life is opposed to it. You cannot have it and align yourself with death and destruction. The Last Jedi is quietly matter-of-fact in its affirming of what love needs to survive and it comes down hard against the darkness, exposing its barrenness and cruelty without moralizing.

That’s not a problematic story; it is the most breathtakingly moral and powerful thing I can imagine and I’m so grateful it exists.

summary: That’s actually so true, I actually think it’s Kylo on one side and Rey on the other. On the left side, If you look at the jaw...
body:
That’s actually so true, I actually think it’s Kylo on one side and Rey on the other. On the left side, If you look at the jaw and the shading of the nose it looks quite large, and the lips are slightly lifted and larger, the chin is a little in showing a face similar to Kylo.

On the right side it’s definitely Rey there is a little shade on the other side to bring out some nose, the lips are smaller than the left side, and there are no signs of furrowing of the eyebrows.

I personally think it’s Kylo and Rey on both sides I could be wrong though!

summary: Soldiers from 96th Mandalorian Tank Division en route during the first major offensive of Mandalorian Ket Corps. The first...
caption:
Soldiers from 96th Mandalorian Tank Division en route during the first major offensive of Mandalorian Ket Corps. The first months of war happened to be relatively easy for mandalorians. Having no trouble in capturing the cities of Ysmair and Yuu’Mori, Ro'shuk’s troops marched on straight to the main port of the planet - Ket-city. However, the lack of supplies that followed unexpectedly soon after the start of the campaign, forced the Corps to stand down and prepare for the desperate defence until the reinforcements arrive. It was only the beginning…

So yeah, I haven’t done anything mandalorian in a while, so here you go! One more pic of our favourite 96th division (I need to learn how to draw tanks tho, ‘cause up until now the 96th has been a tank division only in name, lol). And once again I wasn’t too keen on drawing a detailed background , but at least I made an effort to put more than one character on the pic, yaaaay~
Also, fyi, the pose and angle were mostly inspired by this photo of german soldier during the battle of the Bulge (with a totaly opposite mood tho, lol). But anyway, I hope you enjoy the pic!

Musical inspiration:
AC/DC - Dogs of War
